TIME CONSTANTS, USED TO SEPARATE PROTONS AND
ALPHAS.
KI(TL) CRYSTAL SCINTILLATOR, 10 MM THICK AND

.BACKGROUND AND ATTENUATION OF PRIMARY NEUTRONS IN

ACCURATE TO WITHIN 7 PERCENT, FROM THE JUDGEMENT

SYSTEM. THE COMBINED EFFECT OF THE LATTER TWO WAS
GENERALLY LESS THAN 10 PERCENT.
.TOTAL ERROR WAS +-12 PERCENT (15 PERCENT AT 13.7
MEV).

x4freetext: .TRANSITION TO FIRST EXCITED STATE OF CL-36.
.KI DETECTOR ALSO SERVED AS SAMPLE.
GAMMA RAYS DETECTED IN COINCIDENCE WITH THE
EMITTED ALPHA PARTICLES.
KI(TL) CRYSTAL SCINTILLATOR, 2.5 CM
BY 2.5 CM, USED AS SAMPLE AND DETECTOR OF
PRIMARY ALPHAS.
NAI(TL) SCINTILLATOR, 7.6 CM BY 7.6 CM, USED
TO DETECT COINCIDENT GAMMAS. ABSOLUTE FULL
ENERGY PEAK EFFICIENCY MEASURED IN SAME
GEOMETRY USING BETA-GAMMA AND GAMMA-GAMMA
TECHNIQUES TAKING SELF ABSORPTION IN THE KI
CRYSTAL INTO ACCOUNT.
PLASTIC SCINTILLATORS WITH DIMENSIONS 3*3 MM
AND 10*15 MM USED TO DETERMINE THE ABSOLUTE
NEUTRON FLUX.
FROM NEUDADA. GRAPHICAL DATA GIVEN IN THE
PUBLICATION.
.CORRECTION DUE TO MEASURED ANISOTROPY OF EMISSION
OF 0.79 MEV GAMMA FROM CL-36 OF +6 PERCENT.
.CORRECTION MADE FOR FINITE WIDTH OF DETECTION
WINDOW FOR GAMMAS IN NAI CRYSTAL AND FOR THE
INTERFERENCE OF GAMMAS FROM OTHER GROUPS.
.CORRECTION DUE TO NEUTRONS SCATTERED FROM SHIELDING
OF GAMMA COUNTER, NEUTRON COUNTER AND KI CRYSTAL
INTO THE PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR FLUX MONITOR OF
+15 PERCENT.
.ERROR IN NEUTRON FLUX VALUES OF +-12 PERCENT, DUE
LARGELY TO INSCATTERING FROM VARIOUS SHIELDS.
.ERROR IN ABSOLUTE EFFICIENCY OF GAMMA COUNTER,
INCLUDING EFFECTS OF SELF-ABSORPTION IN THE KI
CRYSTAL, ESTIMATED TO BE LESS THAN +-10 PERCENT.
.FURTHER SOURCES OF ERROR INCLUDE POOR STATISTICS
ELECTRONIC LOSSES AND ERRORS IN WIDTH AND POSITION
OF GAMMA WINDOWS, BACKGROUND SUBTRACTION, ASSUMED
OR MEASURED BRANCHING RATIOS AND ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION
OF GAMMA RAYS. THE COMBINED ERROR DUE TO THESE
SOURCES WAS AT MOST +-10 PERCENT.
.TOTAL ESTIMATED UNCERTAINTIES FROM 15 TO 30 PERCENT.
.UNCERTAINTIES IN UNNORMALIZED DATA 10 TO 15 PERCENT.
